=head1 Procedure

=begin html
<PRE>
Step 10. Enable MLDv2 on the HUT.
Step 11. Call ListenerAPI (S1, I1, M1, INCLUDE, {S1}) on the HUT.
Step 12. Observe the packets on all networks.
Step 13. Call ListenerAPI (S2, I1, M2, EXCLUDE, {S2}) on the HUT.
Step 14. Observe the packets on all networks.
Step 15. TR1 transmits MLDv2 Multicast Address Specific Query message A for M1.
    -----
    IPv6 Header
        IPv6 Hop Limit                  = 1
        IPv6 Source Address             = TR1 Link-local Address
        IPv6 Destination Address        = M1
    Hop-by-Hop Options Header
        Router Alert Option
    ICMPv6 Header (MLD Query)
        Maximum Response Code           = 1000
        Multicast Address               = M1
        S Flag                          = 0
        QRV                             = 2
        QQIC                            = 125
        Number of Sources               = 0
    -----
Step 16. Observe the packets on all networks.
Step 17. TR1 transmits MLDv2 Multicast Address Specific Query message B for M2.
    -----
    IPv6 Header
        IPv6 Hop Limit                  = 1
        IPv6 Source Address             = TR1 Link-local Address
        IPv6 Destination Address        = M2
    Hop-by-Hop Options Header
        Router Alert Option
    ICMPv6 Header (MLD Query)
        Maximum Response Code           = 1000
        Multicast Address               = M2
        S Flag                          = 0
        QRV                             = 2
        QQIC                            = 125
        Number of Sources               = 0
    -----
Step 18. Observe the packets on all networks.
</PRE>

=end html

